---
By: Mohandas Gandhi
Locus:
  Page: 121
  Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Emotions
---
In the march toward Truth, anger, selfishness, hatred, naturally give way,
for otherwise Truth would be impossible to attain. A man who is swayed by
negative emotions may have good enough intentions, may be truthful in word,
but he will never find the truth.
